1
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
"Double Helix"

2
00:01:13,760 --> 00:01:15,799
I'm... I'm trying to be nice.

3
00:01:16,319 --> 00:01:18,319
Don't... don't push your luck.

4
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:19,439
Believe it or not,

5
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:20,680
today I'll...

6
00:01:22,799 --> 00:01:23,879
What... what are you doing?

7
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:25,480
I'll say it again.

8
00:01:25,719 --> 00:01:26,519
My performance contract

9
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:28,055
only specifies the setlist and duration.

10
00:01:28,079 --> 00:01:29,479
It doesn't include taking requests.

11
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,239
Also, don't touch me
without permission.

12
00:01:33,079 --> 00:01:34,359
It's common courtesy.

13
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:37,840
Guys,

14
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:39,760
let's drink.

15
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:41,720
Sorry about that, everyone.

16
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,319
Sorry for the disturbance.

17
00:01:43,439 --> 00:01:44,999
Next, I'd like to play a song for you all.

18
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,000
It's one I wrote myself.

19
00:01:46,439 --> 00:01:48,680
Alright! Alright! Alright!

20
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:25,800
Let me treat you to a late-night snack.

21
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:27,520
I've told you many times.

22
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:29,096
I don't want to have
anything to do with you.

23
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,920
So it's useless for you
to keep pestering me.

24
00:02:32,759 --> 00:02:34,080
It's just a meal.

25
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:36,720
I'm not asking for your hand in marriage.

26
00:02:36,879 --> 00:02:37,879
Move.

27
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,039
What do you want to eat?

28
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:47,300
(Episode 3: Stolen Happiness, I'm Willing)

29
00:02:48,199 --> 00:02:49,199
Yichen.

30
00:02:50,599 --> 00:02:51,599
Um...

31
00:02:51,759 --> 00:02:54,240
Do you have any plans after graduation?

32
00:02:54,919 --> 00:02:57,000
If all goes well, I'll
probably stay here for now.

33
00:02:57,301 --> 00:02:58,735
My younger brother got into
school here two years ago.

34
00:02:58,759 --> 00:03:00,599
This way, it's easier to look after him.

35
00:03:01,879 --> 00:03:02,759
Have you ever thought about

36
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:04,080
checking out my family's company?

37
00:03:04,199 --> 00:03:06,639
I heard my dad say there's a
position that's perfect for you.

38
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,919
Xiao Chen, come back quickly.

39
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,199
Your dad is dying.

40
00:03:13,039 --> 00:03:14,039
Yichen.

41
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:22,639
Dad's death was so sudden.

42
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:26,080
We were consumed by the terrible news,

43
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:29,159
drowning in sorrow,

44
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,599
unable to save ourselves.

45
00:04:05,199 --> 00:04:06,199
Bro.

46
00:04:07,199 --> 00:04:08,199
Are you still

47
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:10,120
trying to contact Lu Feng?

48
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,600
Let me introduce you.

49
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,040
Your fiancée.

50
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:09,920
Whose?

51
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:13,415
The youngest daughter of the
Lancheng real estate tycoon.

52
00:05:13,439 --> 00:05:14,439
She's your age.

53
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:16,639
Our family's new internet
company in Lancheng

54
00:05:16,839 --> 00:05:17,839
needs their support.

55
00:05:21,399 --> 00:05:22,879
What does that have to do with me?

56
00:05:23,959 --> 00:05:26,800
Dad said if you do what you're
told and get engaged to her,

57
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:29,920
our company in Lancheng
will be yours to manage.

58
00:05:34,839 --> 00:05:35,879
Tell her to get lost.

59
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,680
Lu Feng.

60
00:05:39,759 --> 00:05:40,759
It's another way of saying,

61
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:42,319
you can fly back home.

62
00:06:08,399 --> 00:06:09,576
In the Chinese-American community,

63
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:12,079
Lu Feng, the second son
of a famous entrepreneur,

64
00:06:12,399 --> 00:06:13,879
is twenty-four years old.

65
00:06:14,279 --> 00:06:15,519
He and a well-known designer

66
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:17,639
suddenly announced
their engagement recently.

67
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:20,399
It's said they fell in love at first sight.

68
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:57,800
I'm sorry.

69
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:00,839
Bro.

70
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,879
He's not worth your grief. Forget him.

71
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:04,800
You're right.

72
00:07:05,013 --> 00:07:06,013
He forgot long ago.

73
00:07:06,453 --> 00:07:07,453
He's cured.

74
00:07:08,079 --> 00:07:09,399
He can marry a woman now.

75
00:07:10,319 --> 00:07:11,879
Too bad I'm not as capable as him.

76
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,360
To forget so completely.

77
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:14,680
Bro.

78
00:07:14,959 --> 00:07:16,560
Let me take you somewhere, okay?

79
00:07:16,839 --> 00:07:17,480
Where?

80
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:18,840
You'll see when we get there.

81
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:20,040
Two beers.

82
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:21,480
Bro, sit.

83
00:07:23,279 --> 00:07:24,839
It's my treat today.

84
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:27,680
Let's drink our hearts out.
We're not leaving till we're drunk.

85
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,040
Okay.

86
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:04,759
Bro, I'm going to the restroom.

87
00:08:14,519 --> 00:08:15,519
Yichen.

88
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,879
You are...?

89
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:23,800
Xiao Chen.

90
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:26,680
Lu Feng.

91
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:32,360
Lu Feng... Bro...

92
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:34,279
I'm not Lu Feng.

93
00:08:34,559 --> 00:08:35,159
Bro.

94
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,320
Lu Feng.

95
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,720
Bro, don't be like this.

96
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,360
Lu Feng.

97
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:05,360
You have an older brother?

98
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,000
What's wrong with him?

99
00:09:07,279 --> 00:09:09,199
It's like he's been through
some kind of trauma.

100
00:09:10,879 --> 00:09:11,879
Qin Lang.

101
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,159
You like men, right?

102
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:19,200
To avoid any unnecessary misunderstandings,

103
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,600
let me reiterate.

104
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:26,720
You're the only one I like.

105
00:09:39,679 --> 00:09:40,679
What's wrong?

106
00:09:41,559 --> 00:09:42,679
But I don't like men.

107
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:44,600
And I certainly don't like you.

108
00:09:50,399 --> 00:09:51,559
You just saw him.

109
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:54,720
My brother and I look
quite alike, don't we?

110
00:09:56,559 --> 00:09:57,559
So,

111
00:09:58,559 --> 00:10:00,320
why don't you try liking
my brother instead?

112
00:10:02,167 --> 00:10:03,743
Do you have any idea what you're saying?

113
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,480
My brother has been through a lot.

114
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:09,159
He... fell in love with an
irresponsible and selfish man.

115
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:11,759
That guy just left back
then without a word.

116
00:10:12,233 --> 00:10:13,993
And now, that guy is
suddenly getting married.

117
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:17,320
My brother keeps saying he doesn't care,

118
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,879
but I know he hasn't
forgotten for a single day.

119
00:10:20,399 --> 00:10:21,399
Everyone says

120
00:10:21,639 --> 00:10:23,278
the best way to get over a relationship

121
00:10:23,279 --> 00:10:25,039
is to start a new one.

122
00:10:25,799 --> 00:10:26,799
So, Qin Lang,

123
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:31,000
why don't you try dating my brother?

124
00:10:48,399 --> 00:10:49,919
So this is your answer to me.

125
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,200
Fine.

126
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:02,759
I'm not the shameless type

127
00:11:03,279 --> 00:11:04,679
who'll cling to you no matter what.

128
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:06,840
As for your brother...

129
00:11:07,559 --> 00:11:08,600
he's not bad.

130
00:11:09,279 --> 00:11:10,279
I'll think about it.

131
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,240
As for you,

132
00:11:17,219 --> 00:11:18,219
do as you please.

133
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,600
Okay.

134
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:54,840
Xiao Chen.

135
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,279
Lu Feng.

136
00:11:57,679 --> 00:11:58,679
You're awake.

137
00:11:59,639 --> 00:12:00,759
You are...?

138
00:12:01,399 --> 00:12:02,399
Last night,

139
00:12:02,919 --> 00:12:04,359
you had too much to drink at my bar.

140
00:12:04,399 --> 00:12:05,399
You don't remember?

141
00:12:08,919 --> 00:12:09,919
Um...

142
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:11,320
I'm sorry.

143
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:12,600
No, I mean...

144
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:13,840
Thank you.

145
00:12:14,759 --> 00:12:15,759
Don't mention it.

146
00:12:16,919 --> 00:12:17,919
I helped you

147
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:19,279
for a reason.

148
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:31,720
Last night,

149
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:34,720
I fell in love with you at first sight.

150
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:37,399
Could you give me a chance

151
00:12:38,279 --> 00:12:39,599
for us to get to know each other?

152
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:03,720
Eat.

153
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:06,360
That day,

154
00:13:07,279 --> 00:13:08,720
I didn't reject Qin Lang.

155
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,480
I was in too much pain.

156
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:14,639
I needed something new

157
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:18,039
to distract myself from Lu Feng.

158
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:25,960
"Your brother loves my cooking."

159
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:40,720
My relationship with Qin Lang

160
00:13:41,759 --> 00:13:43,639
started inexplicably like that.

161
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:48,747
Most of the time,
we just talked.

162
00:13:48,772 --> 00:13:50,060
[He's complaining
about being left on read]

163
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,799
Qin Lang is a great guy.

164
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,879
Considerate and gentle.

165
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,440
We really clicked.

166
00:13:57,679 --> 00:13:59,959
Like old friends who've known
each other for a long time.

167
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:08,840
Happy birthday to you.

168
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:11,759
Happy birthday to you.

169
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:15,240
Happy birthday to you.

170
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:18,759
Happy birthday to you.

171
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:20,320
Thank you.

172
00:14:30,639 --> 00:14:31,639
Alright.

173
00:14:31,919 --> 00:14:32,919
Time to cut the cake.

174
00:14:36,679 --> 00:14:37,679
Yichen.

175
00:14:39,279 --> 00:14:40,279
What's wrong?

176
00:14:42,879 --> 00:14:43,879
Nothing.

177
00:14:44,639 --> 00:14:45,639
This piece is for you.

178
00:14:45,759 --> 00:14:46,879
It has the almonds you like.

179
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:50,240
I specifically asked Shen Chao to order it.

180
00:14:52,639 --> 00:14:53,639
Thanks.

181
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:54,960
But...

182
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:56,159
I don't like almonds.

183
00:14:56,879 --> 00:14:57,879
He does, though.

184
00:15:01,879 --> 00:15:02,879
Thanks, bro.

185
00:15:08,379 --> 00:15:09,379
Delicious.

186
00:15:33,879 --> 00:15:34,879
Get in.

187
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:37,039
Bro, get in the car.

188
00:15:37,799 --> 00:15:38,919
Aren't you coming with us?

189
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:40,416
I made plans with a friend.

190
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,056
We're pulling an all-nighter
playing games at his place.

191
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:43,080
It's not on the way.

192
00:15:44,799 --> 00:15:45,799
You get in, too.

193
00:15:45,919 --> 00:15:47,279
I'll take your brother home first,

194
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:49,480
and then I'll take you
to your friend's place.

195
00:15:50,919 --> 00:15:51,919
Get in, bro.

196
00:15:56,279 --> 00:15:57,039
As for you,

197
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,398
you're just responsible
for getting my brother

198
00:15:58,399 --> 00:15:59,639
back to school safely.

199
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,080
Go on.

200
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:10,559
Go on, don't drag your feet.

201
00:16:35,399 --> 00:16:37,039
Your brother is so good to you.

202
00:16:38,879 --> 00:16:40,480
He can't bear to see anyone hurt you.

203
00:16:40,799 --> 00:16:42,279
But he has no problem hurting others.

204
00:16:42,759 --> 00:16:43,759
Including himself.

205
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:47,080
Qin Lang.

206
00:16:47,399 --> 00:16:48,719
Why are you suddenly saying this?

207
00:16:50,639 --> 00:16:51,320
It's nothing.

208
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:54,320
I just saw how close
you and your brother are.

209
00:16:54,519 --> 00:16:55,519
And it got me thinking.

210
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:05,000
When are you planning to finish school?

211
00:17:05,079 --> 00:17:06,720
How's the job hunt going?

212
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:10,119
I'm considering a few decent companies.

213
00:17:10,651 --> 00:17:11,691
But I haven't decided yet.

214
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:14,240
Take your time. Don't rush.

215
00:17:22,359 --> 00:17:23,359
Well, take care.

216
00:17:24,039 --> 00:17:25,039
Okay.

217
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:58,519
Qin Lang.

218
00:18:21,279 --> 00:18:22,799
What are you doing here?

219
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:26,680
What took you so long?

220
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:29,720
My bad.

221
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,160
I'm late.

222
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:38,440
Let's go.

223
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:58,559
Yi-chen.

224
00:18:58,759 --> 00:18:59,759
Don't stay out too late.

225
00:18:59,906 --> 00:19:01,025
Text me when you get there.

226
00:19:12,799 --> 00:19:16,272
[He's making himself crash out
looking up Lu Feng news on the internet]

227
00:19:22,499 --> 00:19:23,973
[Conversation with his brother]

228
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,400
Why am I at your place?

229
00:19:56,599 --> 00:19:57,599
You drank too much.

230
00:19:57,920 --> 00:19:59,160
Shen Chao brought you back.

231
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:00,880
He didn't know where you live.

232
00:20:05,799 --> 00:20:06,799
Didn't you say...

233
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:09,320
you were going to a
friend's to play video games?

234
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:10,920
How did you end up this drunk?

235
00:20:12,519 --> 00:20:13,519
Stay out of it.

236
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,400
I could've stayed out of it before.

237
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,160
But not anymore.

238
00:20:19,599 --> 00:20:21,399
After all, I'm dating
your brother, aren't I?

239
00:20:22,079 --> 00:20:23,559
Your brother cares about you so much.

240
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:24,760
As your brother's boyfriend,

241
00:20:24,799 --> 00:20:26,240
I have to love what he loves.

242
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:27,960
- Plus...
- Get out.

243
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:33,880
Where are you going?

244
00:20:35,952 --> 00:20:36,952
What?

245
00:20:37,839 --> 00:20:40,095
Are you not happy that your
brother and I are getting along?

246
00:20:40,119 --> 00:20:41,559
Isn't this what you wanted me to do?

247
00:20:42,799 --> 00:20:43,480
Shut up.

248
00:20:43,799 --> 00:20:45,880
Shut up, shut up, shut up!

249
00:20:46,799 --> 00:20:49,119
Tell me. Am I not doing enough?

250
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:52,000
Or do you want me and your
brother to be together forever?

251
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:54,640
So you can watch us be
all lovey-dovey every day?

252
00:20:55,359 --> 00:20:56,359
Yi-chen.

253
00:20:57,279 --> 00:20:58,359
Ask yourself.

254
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:01,880
Is this really what you want?

255
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:04,640
I'm begging you, don't
say it. I'm begging you.

256
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,200
Why are you crying?

257
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:10,560
I thought you didn't like me.

258
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:11,960
I don't!

259
00:21:48,279 --> 00:21:49,279
It's my fault.

260
00:21:50,079 --> 00:21:52,656
I never should have gone along
with your nonsense from the start.

261
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:54,160
Let's go tell your brother the truth.

262
00:21:54,759 --> 00:21:55,880
That we lied to him.

263
00:21:56,279 --> 00:21:57,279
Okay?

264
00:21:59,279 --> 00:22:00,279
No.

265
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:02,880
My brother won't be able to take it.

266
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:05,279
He can't get hurt again.

267
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:07,560
The longer we drag this
out, the more he'll be hurt.

268
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:10,119
I don't just fall for any guy I see.

269
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:12,996
The person I've liked from the very
beginning has only ever been you.

270
00:22:16,359 --> 00:22:18,919
Do you expect me to lie to your
brother for the rest of my life?

271
00:22:19,559 --> 00:22:20,559
Is that even possible?

272
00:22:21,559 --> 00:22:22,799
Is that fair to me?

273
00:22:23,519 --> 00:22:24,720
Is that fair to your brother?

274
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:27,799
Your brother has been scarred by love.

275
00:22:27,824 --> 00:22:29,344
It's all because of that guy named Lu.

276
00:22:30,119 --> 00:22:31,960
It has nothing to do with you or me.

277
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:34,720
If you keep messing
around with me like this,

278
00:22:35,559 --> 00:22:36,960
I'll go find that Lu guy.

279
00:22:37,839 --> 00:22:39,159
And get revenge for your brother.

280
00:22:39,799 --> 00:22:41,119
Then everyone can move on.

281
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,200
Don't do anything crazy.

282
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:45,920
Yi-chen.

283
00:22:47,519 --> 00:22:48,519
Bro.

284
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:50,880
Yi-chen.

285
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:53,055
I brought you your favorite almond cookies.

286
00:22:53,079 --> 00:22:54,680
Qin Lang was just talking nonsense.

287
00:22:54,799 --> 00:22:55,880
He's still drunk.

288
00:22:56,559 --> 00:22:57,680
He'll be good to you.

289
00:22:58,079 --> 00:22:59,079
Right, Qin Lang?

290
00:22:59,559 --> 00:23:00,559
Yichen.

291
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:01,880
I'm sorry.

292
00:23:03,319 --> 00:23:03,960
Yi-chen.

293
00:23:04,079 --> 00:23:04,880
Bro, listen to me.

294
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:05,960
Yi-chen.

295
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:07,400
Don't get upset.

296
00:23:07,960 --> 00:23:08,960
Just listen to me first.

297
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:10,880
Qin Lang and I...

298
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:12,720
have always just been friends.

299
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:14,535
We don't have feelings for each other.

300
00:23:14,559 --> 00:23:15,559
That's not true, Bro.

301
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:16,880
He likes you.

302
00:23:17,319 --> 00:23:18,400
He'll be good to you.

303
00:23:21,039 --> 00:23:22,160
When did you two meet?

304
00:23:22,559 --> 00:23:25,720
From the first day he
started working at my bar,

305
00:23:26,519 --> 00:23:27,960
I knew I liked him.

306
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:30,559
I know Yi-chen has feelings for me too.

307
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:32,960
But he...

308
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:34,800
would never say yes to me.

309
00:23:35,279 --> 00:23:36,599
But I really like Yi-chen.

310
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:39,240
I like him so, so much.

311
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:41,560
If you like him, why didn't you say yes?

312
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:42,920
Is it because of me?

313
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,735
Did what happened between
me and Lu Feng scare you?

314
00:23:44,759 --> 00:23:45,759
No, Bro.

315
00:23:46,319 --> 00:23:47,319
It's not your fault.

316
00:23:48,039 --> 00:23:50,359
I'm just... not into guys.

317
00:23:50,519 --> 00:23:51,720
It's okay to like him.

318
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:53,640
Don't go against your own heart.

319
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,320
Liking someone is just that.

320
00:23:55,519 --> 00:23:56,519
It's not perverted.

321
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:58,735
And it's not something you can
just give away to someone else.

322
00:23:58,759 --> 00:23:59,759
Understand?

323
00:24:15,759 --> 00:24:16,759
Bro.

324
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:18,920
Why are you so set on working in Lancheng?

325
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:20,519
Is it because of us?

326
00:24:20,759 --> 00:24:21,839
What are you talking about?

327
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:23,255
It's because the company in Lancheng...

328
00:24:23,279 --> 00:24:24,535
offered the best benefits package.

329
00:24:24,559 --> 00:24:26,079
Then why won't you let us see you off?

330
00:24:26,118 --> 00:24:27,798
Am I a child? I don't need to be seen off.

331
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:28,839
Besides,

332
00:24:29,039 --> 00:24:30,479
Qin Lang has to work during the day,

333
00:24:30,559 --> 00:24:31,559
and at the bar at night.

334
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:32,880
And you,

335
00:24:32,960 --> 00:24:33,759
you're about to be a junior.

336
00:24:33,960 --> 00:24:35,400
You should be busy with internships.

337
00:24:35,799 --> 00:24:36,480
But I...

338
00:24:36,759 --> 00:24:37,880
Enough with the 'buts'.

339
00:24:38,759 --> 00:24:40,079
Then call me when you get there.

340
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:41,200
Okay.

341
00:25:03,878 --> 00:25:06,005
(One month later)

342
00:25:07,925 --> 00:25:10,196
(New Employee Information)

343
00:25:16,559 --> 00:25:18,359
Mr. Lu, are we heading home first?

344
00:25:19,799 --> 00:25:20,799
Straight to the office.

345
00:25:21,359 --> 00:25:22,359
Understood.

346
00:25:22,839 --> 00:25:23,999
Let's go to the office first.

347
00:25:24,319 --> 00:25:25,319
Okay.

348
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:33,640
Here he comes, the new boss is here.

349
00:25:40,799 --> 00:25:42,039
Good morning, Mr. Lu.

350
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:52,160
Cheng Yichen.

351
00:25:55,519 --> 00:25:56,519
Long time no see.

352
00:26:21,119 --> 00:26:22,119
Have a seat.

353
00:26:29,519 --> 00:26:30,519
Begin.

354
00:27:25,759 --> 00:27:26,960
You have a girlfriend?

355
00:27:28,279 --> 00:27:29,279
Yeah, I do.

356
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:33,240
Was it that long-haired girl
sitting next to you earlier?

357
00:27:43,079 --> 00:27:44,079
Yes.

358
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:45,880
The handover documents for that project...

359
00:27:46,039 --> 00:27:47,479
you need to look them over again.

360
00:27:49,319 --> 00:27:49,880
That's enough.

361
00:27:50,039 --> 00:27:51,039
Let's go.

362
00:28:04,119 --> 00:28:05,119
Special Assistant Chou.

363
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:07,440
This proposal...

364
00:28:10,473 --> 00:28:13,552
you don't have make such
drastic changes every time.

365
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:15,815
You can just make some minor changes.

366
00:28:15,839 --> 00:28:16,519
Actually,

367
00:28:16,640 --> 00:28:18,840
- you need to learn to integrate...
- Good morning, Mr. Lu.

368
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:21,000
Mr. Lu.

369
00:28:24,839 --> 00:28:27,039
But it just feels like a mess.

370
00:28:27,160 --> 00:28:28,160
Right.

371
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:29,519
This data...

372
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,039
Girlfriend?

373
00:28:38,519 --> 00:28:40,160
You really got a girlfriend?

374
00:28:46,119 --> 00:28:46,799
Chou Cheng.

375
00:28:47,079 --> 00:28:48,639
Bring me Cheng Yichen's file. Now.

376
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:49,799
Right away, Mr. Lu.

377
00:29:26,079 --> 00:29:26,880
Who is it?

378
00:29:27,079 --> 00:29:28,400
Still sleeping at this hour?

379
00:29:30,559 --> 00:29:31,720
I'm sleepy.

380
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:34,240
When you talk to people in that tone,

381
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:36,160
it's easy to give them the wrong idea.

382
00:29:37,839 --> 00:29:38,839
Mr. L-

383
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,000
Mr. Lu.

384
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:42,480
If you're free, come over to my place.

385
00:29:43,119 --> 00:29:44,319
I need you to fix my computer.

386
00:29:45,079 --> 00:29:46,519
I don't know how to fix computers.

387
00:29:47,799 --> 00:29:49,759
Isn't your major computer-related?

388
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,255
You can't even handle
a simple task like this?

389
00:29:51,279 --> 00:29:52,735
How did you even get hired at my company?

390
00:29:52,759 --> 00:29:54,839
My major is Digital Media,

391
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:56,359
not hardware repair.

392
00:29:58,519 --> 00:29:59,720
Just get over here.

393
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:02,119
What's the problem?

394
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:04,160
We can troubleshoot it online.

395
00:30:04,960 --> 00:30:06,480
My laptop won't turn on.

396
00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:08,720
If there are no important files on it,

397
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:11,400
then just format the drive.

398
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:13,480
I tried.

399
00:30:13,559 --> 00:30:15,799
What does the screen say?

400
00:30:16,319 --> 00:30:17,480
It says 'Cannot format'.

401
00:30:20,039 --> 00:30:21,279
Okay, find a screwdriver.

402
00:30:25,799 --> 00:30:26,519
And then?

403
00:30:26,799 --> 00:30:27,960
Flip the back cover over.

404
00:30:33,119 --> 00:30:34,119
See anything?

405
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:35,640
Describe it.

406
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:37,480
It's smoking.

407
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:39,160
You better get over here.

408
00:30:54,039 --> 00:30:55,720
What's taking so long? Hurry up.

409
00:30:56,359 --> 00:30:57,440
Stop dawdling.

410
00:30:58,880 --> 00:30:59,880
Where's the computer?

411
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:14,039
Did water get in it?

412
00:31:31,799 --> 00:31:32,799
Can it be fixed?

413
00:31:34,759 --> 00:31:36,279
You should just send it in for repairs.

414
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:38,720
I'll have Chou Cheng come by later.

415
00:31:46,359 --> 00:31:47,719
Sit down. Have something to drink.

416
00:32:07,079 --> 00:32:09,920
This place is decorated pretty nicely.

417
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:12,160
My sister used to live here.

418
00:32:12,799 --> 00:32:14,799
I moved in before I even
had a chance to clean up.

419
00:32:23,960 --> 00:32:24,960
I should get going.

420
00:32:27,759 --> 00:32:28,880
This... this isn't mine.

421
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:34,480
It must be my sister's.

422
00:32:35,319 --> 00:32:36,319
Think about it.

423
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:38,400
I just moved in a few days ago.

424
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:41,360
It wouldn't be surprising if it were yours.

425
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:42,920
You have a fiancée, after all.

426
00:32:43,039 --> 00:32:44,039
Fiancée.

427
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:46,480
In another half a month,

428
00:32:47,039 --> 00:32:47,720
you'll see

429
00:32:47,721 --> 00:32:49,240
the news of our broken engagement.

430
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:52,480
It was all an act from the beginning.

431
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:53,680
Everyone knows.

432
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:55,440
She needs her dad's business.

433
00:32:55,960 --> 00:32:57,440
My dad needs her dad's money.

434
00:32:58,279 --> 00:32:59,279
And I...

435
00:32:59,960 --> 00:33:00,799
needed to come back to the country.

436
00:33:00,960 --> 00:33:02,240
Everyone gets what they want.

437
00:33:02,359 --> 00:33:03,480
A win-win-win deal.

438
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:11,319
So... want to think about it?

439
00:33:18,279 --> 00:33:19,640
Th-think about what?

440
00:33:20,799 --> 00:33:21,799
Think about...

441
00:33:23,039 --> 00:33:24,535
breaking up with
your current girlfriend...

442
00:33:24,559 --> 00:33:26,039
and getting back together with me.

443
00:33:29,599 --> 00:33:31,960
I won't mind that you've
dated other people.

444
00:33:34,039 --> 00:33:35,559
You seem busy. I'll get going.

445
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:37,976
Are you too embarrassed to say something?

446
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:38,759
If you are,

447
00:33:38,839 --> 00:33:39,880
I can do it for you.

448
00:33:41,319 --> 00:33:42,160
To compensate her,

449
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:44,000
I can even give her a
promotion and a raise.

450
00:33:45,599 --> 00:33:46,599
I'm leaving.

451
00:33:47,359 --> 00:33:49,079
Why don't we grab a bite before you go?

452
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:50,000
I'm not hungry.

453
00:33:50,119 --> 00:33:51,119
Well, I am.

454
00:33:51,759 --> 00:33:53,279
I'll go change. I'll be quick.

455
00:33:54,079 --> 00:33:54,680
Sit.

456
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,000
Don't you dare leave.

457
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:12,639
Order whatever you want.

458
00:34:14,880 --> 00:34:16,960
I'll have this.

459
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:18,760
This one.

460
00:34:18,840 --> 00:34:19,840
And this one.

461
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:23,039
You're not paying, so
what are you afraid of?

462
00:34:23,559 --> 00:34:25,239
I'll eat whatever I want.

463
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:27,840
Bring me a glass of your
most expensive red wine.

464
00:34:30,239 --> 00:34:31,079
I'll take the wine.

465
00:34:31,239 --> 00:34:32,519
Get him a glass of orange juice.

466
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:33,960
Right away, sir.

467
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:37,920
Enjoy your meal.

468
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:48,760
Is it good?

469
00:34:59,039 --> 00:35:00,039
Cheng Yichen.

470
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:03,360
Mr... Mr. Lu.

471
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:04,519
Come on, eat with us.

472
00:35:04,599 --> 00:35:05,599
Mr. Lu is treating.

473
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:20,400
Waiter.

474
00:35:21,159 --> 00:35:22,359
More place settings, please.

475
00:35:26,559 --> 00:35:27,559
Thanks.

476
00:35:28,119 --> 00:35:29,119
Thank you.

477
00:35:29,199 --> 00:35:30,199
He's paying?

478
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:36,000
Here, try this.

479
00:35:45,679 --> 00:35:46,960
You've got some on your face.

480
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:54,760
Whose girlfriend are you, anyway?

481
00:35:55,199 --> 00:35:56,495
How dare you, in front of Xiao Chen,

482
00:35:56,519 --> 00:35:58,039
flirt with another man?

483
00:35:59,719 --> 00:36:00,719
I...

484
00:36:00,872 --> 00:36:02,392
This is how your girlfriend is acting,

485
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:04,840
and you still don't want
to break up with her?

486
00:36:08,239 --> 00:36:08,920
You...

487
00:36:09,039 --> 00:36:11,159
You told the boss I'm your girlfriend?

488
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:13,615
Don't tell me you've had
a secret crush on me...

489
00:36:13,639 --> 00:36:14,679
and I just never knew?

490
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:17,360
Cheng Yichen, you despicable jerk.

491
00:36:22,679 --> 00:36:23,679
My apologies.

492
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:25,400
It seems I've misunderstood.

493
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:26,880
Waiter.

494
00:36:27,039 --> 00:36:28,039
The menu.

495
00:36:34,719 --> 00:36:35,880
Well, we'll be going then.

496
00:36:36,719 --> 00:36:37,719
Let me give you a ride.

497
00:36:39,039 --> 00:36:39,880
Old classmate.

498
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,000
No, thanks.

499
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:42,800
It's on my way.

500
00:36:44,079 --> 00:36:45,079
Come with me.

501
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:47,839
W-well, we're leaving now, Yichen.

502
00:36:47,840 --> 00:36:48,880
Thanks for dinner, Mr. Lu.

503
00:36:49,079 --> 00:36:50,360
Bye-bye. Let's go, let's go.

504
00:36:58,480 --> 00:36:59,480
Sha-sha.

505
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:01,639
You don't actually like Yichen, do you?

506
00:37:41,519 --> 00:37:42,519
I'm thirsty.

507
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:44,560
Let's go to your place
for a glass of water.

508
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:52,039
What?

509
00:37:52,119 --> 00:37:53,159
Just a moment.

510
00:38:00,559 --> 00:38:02,000
Xiao Chen, what are you doing?

511
00:38:02,840 --> 00:38:03,960
Is someone in there?

512
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:06,480
Open the door.

513
00:38:07,159 --> 00:38:08,159
Cheng Yichen.

514
00:38:23,599 --> 00:38:24,880
You share this place, right?

515
00:38:26,280 --> 00:38:27,440
It seems nice.

516
00:38:27,773 --> 00:38:28,773
Just a little small.

517
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:32,040
Why don't you live in a nicer apartment?

518
00:38:32,119 --> 00:38:34,400
The rent around here is ridiculously high.

519
00:38:34,960 --> 00:38:36,919
For my first year after
graduation, living here...

520
00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:38,639
is already pretty good.

521
00:38:39,519 --> 00:38:41,400
My roommate isn't home much,

522
00:38:41,519 --> 00:38:44,159
so I basically have the place to myself.

523
00:38:48,119 --> 00:38:49,360
What would you like to drink?

524
00:38:49,519 --> 00:38:50,519
There's no red wine.

525
00:38:53,647 --> 00:38:54,727
I'd like...

526
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:57,280
orange juice.

527
00:38:59,760 --> 00:39:00,960
Make yourself at home.

528
00:39:41,639 --> 00:39:42,639
How about...

529
00:39:43,199 --> 00:39:44,440
we watch a movie?

530
00:39:45,559 --> 00:39:47,359
- You...
- I haven't seen a movie in a long time.

531
00:39:48,119 --> 00:39:50,400
Aren't you... busy?

532
00:39:52,239 --> 00:39:54,360
I was planning on taking
a break today anyway.

533
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:46,880
Not sentimental at all.

534
00:40:47,679 --> 00:40:49,079
Truly the work of a master.

535
00:40:49,880 --> 00:40:51,400
The more the audience suffers,

536
00:40:52,420 --> 00:40:53,880
the colder the camera becomes.

537
00:40:58,519 --> 00:40:59,880
True suffering...

538
00:41:01,599 --> 00:41:03,639
is something you
can't even put into words.
